NZBGet is a binary newsgrabber, which downloads files from Usenet
based on information given in nzb-files. A description of the nzb
format is available at http://docs.newzbin.com/

It offers the following features:

* Console interface, using either a plain text, a coloured text or
  a fully interactive ncurses interface
* Basic client/server model, allowing easy additions to the download
  queue.
* Bandwidth throttling
* Multiple servers
* Multiple connections
